The Benelux governments nationalize part of the Fortis bank
The Benelux states are helping the Belgian-Hollanda bank, as the first European banking institution in distress as a result of the snowball effect of the credit market crisis in the United States, and partly nationalising it. The three countries are supporting this financial and insurance institution, which also has interests in Hungary, at an amount of EUR 11.2 billion.
